cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper discusses the use of Linear Support Vector Machines (SVMs) trained on HOG features in visual perception tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores the interactions between feature extraction and learning processes, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of preserving second-order statistics and locality of interactions, which are concepts in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
